      "message": "Yeah  I thought about putting it inline, but I thought the nested list comprehensions got a little too busy since there has to be a second layer. I felt that it might be clearer to just have the for-loops even though it requires leaving the file to read.\n```\n[\n    [  # \u003c-- have to use a nested list comp to get the arch from the list\n        filegroup(\n            name \u003d \"libclang_rt_%s_%s_%s\" % (prefix, os, arch),\n            srcs \u003d [\":clang\"],\n            output_group \u003d \"libclang_rt_%s_%s_%s\" % (prefix, os, arch),\n        )\n        for arch in arches\n    ]\n    for os, arches in {\n        \"android\": [\n            \"arm\",\n            \"arm64\",\n            \"x86\",\n            \"x86_64\",\n        ],\n        \"linux\": [\n            \"bionic_x86_64\",\n            \"glibc_x86\",\n            \"glibc_x86_64\",\n            \"musl_x86\",\n            \"musl_x86_64\",\n        ],\n    }.items()\n    for prefix in [\n        \"builtins\",\n        \"ubsan_minimal\",\n    ]\n]\n```",
